.TH SHOAL-MCP 1 "July 2026" "Shoal 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shoal-mcp \- expose Shoal through the Model Context Protocol
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shoal-mcp
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs an MCP server on standard input and output, connected to a Shoal kernel.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-socket " PATH"
Connect to PATH.
.TP
.BI \-\-session " NAME"
Select a session.
.TP
.BI \-\-token " TOKEN"
Authenticate with a capability token.
.TP
.B \-\-local-human
Use local-human authentication.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shoal (1),
.BR shoal-token (1)
